1. Niels Bohr By: Andrew J.Bedard, Joseph Catino

2. Niels Bohrs Background Niels Bohr was born in Copenhagen Denmark in 1885 on october 7. His mother came from a jewish Banking family, and his father was professor at the University of Copenhagen. Niels went University of Copenhagen in 1903, and graduated in 1907. From college he went on the revive his masters in 1909 and his doctorate in 1911. he went to Manchester in 1912 to help Ernest Rutherford in his construction of a Nuclear model of the atom

3. List of Achievements ● Hughes Medal-1921 ● Nobel Prize in Physics-1922 ● Matteucci Medal-1923 ● Franklin Medal-1926 ● Max Planck Medal-1930 ● copley Medal-1938 ● Order Of The Elephant-1947 ● Atoms Of Peace Award-1957 ● Sonning Prize-1957 ● Foreign Member Of The Royal Society-1962

4. The Bohr Model todays model of the aton involves Quantum mechanics, something that Niels Bohr did not have in 1915 when he created his model of the atom.

5. The Bohr and Rutherford model The comparison between Bohr and Rutherford model is that in both models the positive charged nucleus is surrounded be the negitive charged electrons.

6. Contrasting the two models The Rutherford model was the nucleus was positive and was surrounded by electrons. The bohr model
